Vulnerability:
This code suffers from re-entrancy, which enables a malicious contract to exploit it to steal funds from the contract. Re-entrancy occurs when a contract uses an external function or transaction without properly protecting itself against being called again before the previous call has finished. In the example provided, the `fV2` method calls the `_msgSender` contract method to update its internal state. If `_msgSender` is exploited and re-entered, it can steal funds from the `A` contract before the previous call to `_msgSender` completes.

