Vulnerability:
This line of code can be exploited to allow an account to steal from a contract. In this line of code, we create a variable called "hash" and use it to calculate the message ids for 6 different transactions. However, what happens when you try to calculate the 7th transaction? By using a hardcoded value for "last_msg_id", the code will just add it to the previously calculated message ids and try to calculate the 7th transaction. This means that the last_msg_id variable will always contain the most recently executed message id, allowing an attacker to "steal" from the contract. To fix this vulnerability, replace "last_msg_id" with a random number or a value derived from the nonce of the sender account.

